# tape-six-proc — AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

tape-six-proc is a helper for tape-six that runs test files in separate processes (subprocesses) instead of worker threads. Works with Node, Deno, and Bun. Supports TypeScript natively without transpilation. The npm package name is `tape-six-proc` and the CLI command is `tape6-proc`.

## Critical rules

- **ESM-only.** The project is `"type": "module"`. Use `import`/`export` syntax.
- **No transpilation.** Code runs directly in all target runtimes.
- **Do not modify or delete test expectations** without understanding why they changed.
- **Do not add comments or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.
- Do not add dependencies unless absolutely necessary.

## Code style

- Prettier for formatting (see `.prettierrc`).
- No semicolons — enforced by Prettier config.
- Imports at top of file, using `import` syntax.
- The package name is `tape-six-proc` but the CLI command is `tape6-proc`.

## Architecture quick reference

- `bin/tape6-proc.js` — CLI entry point. `--self` prints its path; otherwise delegates to `tape6-proc-node.js`.
- `bin/tape6-proc-node.js` — delegates arg parsing, reporter setup, and file resolution to `tape-six/utils/config.js` (`getOptions`, `initReporter`, `initFiles`, `showInfo`). Adds `--runFileArgs` and `--info`.
- `src/TestWorker.js` — extends `EventServer` from `tape-six`. Spawns child processes via `dollar-shell`, pipes stdout/stderr through stream parsers.

## Verification commands

- `npm test` — run the full test suite (Node)
- `npm run test:bun` — run with Bun
- `npm run test:deno` — run with Deno
- `npm run lint` — Prettier format check

## File layout

- CLI: `bin/tape6-proc.js`, `bin/tape6-proc-node.js`
- Core: `src/TestWorker.js`
- Streams: `src/streams/lines.js`, `src/streams/parse-prefixed-jsonl.js`, `src/streams/wrap-lines.js`
- Tests: `tests/test-*.js`
- Wiki docs: `wiki/` (git submodule)

## When reading the codebase

- Start with `AGENTS.md` for full setup, commands, and architecture.
- Wiki markdown files in `wiki/` contain detailed usage docs.
- `bin/tape6-proc-node.js` and `src/TestWorker.js` are the core modules — read them first.
